    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-05T08:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-05T08:14:00-05:00" n="419"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 322.112.T72/1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Goding</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guayaquil</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-05T08:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1914, 8 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have followed Consular regulations, paragraph 170. There are reports fully and
                    often at the Legation, repeatedly urging immediate action in the Jones case
                    owing to violation of the Ecuadorian laws. The facts are these:</p>
                <pb facs="0398" n="282" xml:id="pg_282"/>
                <p>Chinese shot not more than three months ago. Dozen witnesses prove Jones half
                    block distant from the house when the shot was fired within. Jones’ arrest,
                    imprisonment, and the unnecessary delay shameful, in violation of Ecuadorian
                    laws and constitution opinion of the high court judges and the ablest lawyers.
                    All persons of standing including the highest officials and the President of the
                    Chinese colony are satisfied Jones’ innocence. His arrest and imprisonment
                    disgrace to the United States. Forcible measures imperatively needed at
                    once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Goding</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
